to add some dependancy to a empty folder go to that folder and run "npm init -y" and then run "npm install whateverpackage" to install those packages as dependencies in that npm package/folder. 

require() is same as import().Whatever is importable by import ius importable by require also.Only difference between them is require() executes the module before importing its "exports" object.
whennever we require(module) then we get the exports object of the module in our current scope.


In firebase,

collections contains documents
documents contain data and subcollections.
documents can be reffered by using a reference of its parent collection.